FBIS4-24949 "drchi108_k_94016" FBIS-CHI-94-108 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Domestic Northwest Airlines Flight Crashes Near Xian Domestic Northwest Airlines Flight Crashes Near Xian Foreigners Said Among Dead HK0606060694 Hong Kong AFP in English 0547 GMT 6 Jun 94 HK0606060694 Hong Kong AFP English BFN [Text] Beijing, June 6 (AFP)--A Chinese Northwest Airlines plane carrying 159 people crashed Monday morning near the central tourist city of Xian, a spokesman from the Civil Aviation Administration of China said. Domestic flight WH2303 from Xian in Shaanxi province to Guangzhou in southern Guangdong province took off at 8:12 a.m. (0012 GMT) and lost radio contact with Xian airport eight minutes later, the official said. The plane was carrying 13 crew and 146 passengers, including foreigners, he said. According to aviation sources in Guangzhou, all passengers aboard the Soviet-built plane were killed.
